<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-03T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="581" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d581">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.01/2157: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KAC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-04T01:00:00+03:00">May 4,
                                    1939—1 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received May 3—7 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>216. Foreign Office communiqué issued shortly after midnight states that
                                <persName corresp="#p_LMM1">Litvinov</persName> has been relieved at
                            his own request of his duties as <pb facs="0864" n="758" xml:id="pg_758"/> Commissar for Foreign Affairs, and that his place will be taken by
                                <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> who will continue as
                            Chairman of the Soviet of People’s Commissars.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_KAC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>